07/02/2008
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- The ruling Democratic Party of Socialists (DPS) tapped leader Milo Djukanovic for the post of prime minister-designate on Wednesday (February 6th). Outgoing Prime Minister Zeljko Sturanovic resigned last week due to health problems. Djukanovic has served as prime minister four times, and as president once. (Vijesti - 07/02/08; RTCG, Mina, AP - 06/02/08)
